		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=6695#comment-15119</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Hi Scott! Love your work!!

I would like to see more lessons on how to apply theory/scales/modes to riffs/grooves.

It&#039;s always seemed to me that scales/modes were little more than finger exercises - when the rubber hits the road it always seems that all I end up using are arpeggios or the major pentatonic. i know that i am missing something, but i can&#039;t quite put my finger on it.

I would love to learn to create grooves that don&#039;t just follow the chord patterns, but mine always sound like scale and arpeggio exercises! (root-3rd-5th-7th-shift!)

Thanks again - please keep up the great lessons!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi Scott! Love your work!!</p>
<p>I would like to see more lessons on how to apply theory/scales/modes to riffs/grooves.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s always seemed to me that scales/modes were little more than finger exercises &#8211; when the rubber hits the road it always seems that all I end up using are arpeggios or the major pentatonic. i know that i am missing something, but i can&#8217;t quite put my finger on it.</p>
<p>I would love to learn to create grooves that don&#8217;t just follow the chord patterns, but mine always sound like scale and arpeggio exercises! (root-3rd-5th-7th-shift!)</p>
<p>Thanks again &#8211; please keep up the great lessons!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
