		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/bass-riff-week-1.html#comment-15043</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bob Schad]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 24 Aug 2014 22:06:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=6695#comment-15043</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Cool. I&#039;ve been playing for 40 years now. When I play my upright I play a riff in the lowest position take it up an octave then take it up another octave. on the electric bass take the riff up until you run out of neck then drop it down an octave to finish the riff. This will help you understand your instrument better. Cheers!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Cool. I&#8217;ve been playing for 40 years now. When I play my upright I play a riff in the lowest position take it up an octave then take it up another octave. on the electric bass take the riff up until you run out of neck then drop it down an octave to finish the riff. This will help you understand your instrument better. Cheers!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
